One more Turkey Leftovers recipe
Leftover Turkey Frittata
Leftover turkey and green bean casserole star in this flavorful frittata recipe for a quick entree anytime after the holiday dinner Recipe developed by George Duran for ReadySetEat Hands On: 10 | Total: 25 | Makes: 4 servings (1/4th recipe each) Ingredients:
1 carton (16 oz each) Egg Beaters® Original 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese 1/4 teaspoon dried oregano Dash ground black pepper PAM® Original No-Stick Cooking Spray 1 cup leftover green bean casserole 1 cup chopped cooked turkey breast
Directions
Combine Egg Beaters, cheese, oregano and pepper in small bowl; set aside. Spray 10-inch nonstick saute pan with cooking spray; heat over medium-high heat. Add green beans; cook and stir 2 minutes or until hot. Add turkey; cook 1 minute more. Pour Egg Beaters mixture over turkey and green beans; stir gently. Cover and reduce heat to medium-low; cook 15 minutes or until set.
Nutritional Information:
4 servings (1/4th recipe each) Calories 221; Total Fat 8 g (Saturated Fat 4 g); Cholesterol 48 mg; Sodium 483 mg; Carbohydrate 6 g; (Dietary Fiber 1 g, Sugars 1 g); Protein 28 g; Percent Daily Values*: Vitamin A 26%; Vitamin C 4%; Calcium 13%; Iron 16%
* Percent Daily Values are based on a 2,000 calorie diet.﻿
